#' Bootstrap Transmission Rates
#'
#' This function extracts bootstraps samples of the mean number of transmissions per person.
#'
#' @param results MCMC output as generated by run_mcmc.
#' @param N_samples The number of bootstrap samples to draw.
#' @param uncorrelate If using correlated results, should we first uncorrelate them? (Defualts to TRUE.)
#' @param burnin We discard the first (burnin * 100) percent of the results, if running uncorrelation.
#' @param plot_ci Should we plot the bootstrap confidence intervals of the number of transmissions per person? (Defaults to TRUE.)
#' @return A N_samples x (N + 1) matrix, where N is the number of hosts in the outbreak, and the additional column reports the number of index cases. Each row is one bootstrap sample of the mean number of transmissions per person (or mean number of index cases).
#' @export

